    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - DISASSEMBLE - OUTPUT SHAFT (Figure 11 )</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OUTPUT SHAFT (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400911">Figure 11</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1400911" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400911" filename="../figg14/g1400911.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Output Shaft Components</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. OUTPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. OUTER SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>6. WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>7. NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>8. BEARING CAGE</callout1>
                <callout1>9. BEARING CUPS</callout1>
                <callout1>10. INNER PRELOAD SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>11. THICK SPACER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rear drive shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove output shaft and cage from forward axle housing. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s14009_6.xml" xrefid="f1400901">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount output shaft in vise by clamping yoke in jaws of vise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove nut, washer and yoke.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">It will be necessary to fabricate an adapter (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400912">Figure 12</hotlnk>) to clear the lube trough portion of the bearing retainer
                while pressing the bearings from the shaft. Fabricate the adapter out of 2 5/8" x 1/4" wall steel
                tubing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400912" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400912" filename="../figg14/g1400912.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Adapter</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the adapter onto the output shaft assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400913">Figure 13</hotlnk>). Taking care not to damage threads, press the output shaft
                out of the bearing assembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400913" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400913" filename="../figg14/g1400913.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Position Adapter Onto The Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
